 get a pair pretty easily.<P>As you progress you'll start getting into Hate more (hopefully) and should be able to pick up some EM.<P>I actually didn't hit 200 wisdom until about 52nd   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">  Eventually tho, once you start getting some better general equipment (jewelry, work on getting velium ruby veil, some jasper plat rings, etc.) it will work out that you're probably over 200.<P>A springwood club is a good addition (the strength is a real bonus).<P>Sorry, rambling.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif">  Hope some of this helps.<P>------------------<BR>Salina Grey<BR>Erudite Templar of Pain, Bertoxxulous<BR>Guild Leader, Glory's Path</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Miinxx Jiinxx</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If you dont mind trashing your skyshrine faction id recomend gettting SS armor...good ac decent resists...This is of course on top of the other suggestions made regarding wis. Its a pretty easy camp and you'll be getting real good xp of it as well...<P>Miinxx Jiinxx <BR>52 cleric<BR>Fennin Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Calahad</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">"Some people forget that there are other clerics out there besides high elves. "<P>Bah, what's this?  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kimbera</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">One option for boots may be to go back to leather... Imbued Mithril Studded Boots are AC 6, Wis +2, Cha +2 and made by Wood Elf tailors.  If the 2 Wis is worth the 5 AC difference to you.  I'm not sure how much they go for.<P>High Elf Cultural Smithing may also offer some Wisdom boots for you to use, but probably much more expensive than leathers.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#de