auces". Go to the dock in FP, buy fresh fsh. 1 fish, 1 jug = 2 fish fillets. (trivial at 82). Now go to the last Inn in EC where the lady is that sells all the spell components and buy a dozen or 2 batwings. Then go to the docks and buy an equal # of fresh fish. 1 wing, 1 fish in your spit and you make fish rolls. Trivial at 135. Took me about 2 hours.<P>At 135 baking you can do the 3rd quest easily. This series of quests also nets a shoulder item that gets a little better each time you "upgrade". I currently have a 5ac, 5wis, 5int, 5cr shawl, and am working on the tailoring skill to do the 6th step. The shawl I have is not (yet) better than Adamantite Epoletes, but by #7, it is. #7 is 7ac, 7wis, 7int, 7cr/dr/pr, permanent, STACKABLE effect of Flowing Thought I. Extra mana regen!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">KamuelaTZ</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Your equip at 43 is better then mine was at 52. I also hate boring camps as well so here is what I would do:<P>1)Go to LGuk to xp, work on getting into a tower/assassin group. You'll get good xp and a pair of epolets quickly, got my pair the first hour I was there and a second set dropped 3 hours later.<P>2)Sell that spirit tome, prices vary and have come down but you should get 1-2k for it. Use the money to buy a CGS, see them go for about 900pp and upgrade your wis and AC.<P>3)Buy a pair of quest bracers, should cost you 1k or less.<P>Wis +18<BR>AC ~50 adjusted<BR>Time spent camping: None<P>------------------<BR>Teir' Dal Vicar<BR>Tallon Zek</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">OgreAce</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I'm having major problems doing the 3rd shawl quest- snow griffons seem to be not very plentiful and are always being killed by a 54 druid when I happen to run across one....<P>I know the eggs they drop are the bottleneck, so I figured I would try to collect them before starting with skilling up baking. But I am only on at peak times now, and can't spend all day searching for griffons.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Panteroo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">OgreAce...	<P>Hire a Ranger... seriously... When i was hunting my griffon eggs. I asked for a ranger in the zone who was for hire...<P>I got a /tell almost immediately and struck a deal with him... he got all the experience and all the non-egg loot. I buffed and healed and helped him fight then used atone so he would get the exp... I also paid him 50pp per egg once for the 3 eggs i still needed. As we ran around trying to find griffons on track he killed whatever he wanted. In the end it took 2 hours to get my 3 eggs. The ranger got 150pp + loot drops + 2 yellow bubs of experience (he was level 42). It was the easiest way to do it IMHO<P>Panteroo</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Calahad</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I would like a makeover too please =)<P>level = 30<BR>race = High Elf<BR>wis = 177 in this gear<BR>server = Inny<P>head - Runed Circlet<BR>neck - Gobby Soul Caller<BR>face - Braided Beard of the Coldain<BR>ears - +2 WIS Earring and a +2 AGI Earring<BR>chest - Blood Stained Tunic<BR>shoulders - Adamantium Epaulets<BR>wrists - Bracers of the Revanant and Small Blue Fine Plate Bracer<BR>back/waist - banded , ack<BR>feet - small green fine plate boots<BR>legs/arms - Tizmak arms and leggings<BR>primary - Paw of Opollah<BR>secondary - CGS<BR>range - nada =(<P>I've only been playing a few months, this is my only character.  I know I need to upgrade the back slot.  I was thinking of the Mammoth Cloak, but the Alchemist room was camped the whole time last week I was in the Perma area, and I hear its a nightmare camp for an item that can now be had for ~ 1.5k pp?  The cloak from Karnor's castle seems like a